Based on my thorough analysis of the codebase, I can see the app has an extensive feature set with 30+ Quick Practice cards, rich conversation features, vocabulary SRS, and comprehensive dashboard analytics. Let me identify what's truly missing for fluency building.Now I have a clear picture. The app has 13 speaking cards in QuickPracticeHub but all are single-turn exercises. There's no multi-turn sustained discourse practice outside full conversations. Let me verify:Based on my comprehensive analysis of the codebase, I can now identify the most impactful missing feature. The QuickPracticeHub has 13 speaking cards, but all of them (except QuickRolePlayCard) are single-turn exercises. QuickRolePlayCard has multi-turn scripted exchanges, and QuickOpinionCard is single-turn opinion expression. What's clearly missing is a **multi-turn argumentation practice** where users must construct sustained, logical discourse and respond to counterpoints ‚Äî a critical skill for fluency in professional and academic settings.

```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Add Quick Debate Card for sustained argumentation speaking practice",
  "description": "Add a 'Quick Debate' card to the Speaking tab in QuickPracticeHub. This trains sustained discourse and argumentation ‚Äî a high-value fluency skill not covered by existing cards. QuickOpinionCard is single-turn; QuickRolePlayCard is scripted exchanges. The debate card uniquely requires constructing logical arguments and responding to counterpoints.\n\nFlow: (1) GET /api/pronunciation/debate-topic?difficulty=X returns {statement, counter_argument, context_hint, difficulty}. The LLM generates a controversial statement and a pre-generated counter-argument. (2) User sees the statement, speaks their argument for 30s (Round 1). (3) TTS plays the counter-argument. (4) User responds to it for 30s (Round 2). (5) POST /api/pronunciation/debate/evaluate takes {statement, counter_argument, user_round1_transcript, user_round2_transcript, total_duration_seconds} and returns {argument_structure_score, rebuttal_quality_score, grammar_score, vocabulary_score, coherence_score, overall_score, feedback, model_argument, model_rebuttal}.\n\nBackend: Add 2 endpoints to app/routers/pronunciation.py ‚Äî debate-topic (LLM generates statement + pre-made counter-argument) and debate/evaluate (LLM scores both rounds). Frontend: Create QuickDebateCard.tsx with phases: idle ‚Üí round1_speaking ‚Üí counter_playing ‚Üí round2_speaking ‚Üí evaluating ‚Üí done. Register it in QuickPracticeHub.tsx under the speaking tab. Add API types and functions to api.ts.\n\nNo schema changes needed (no database persistence required for this drill type).",
