## Summary of Changes

**Backend** (`pronunciation.py`): Two new endpoints at the end of the file:
- `GET /scene-description` ‚Äî LLM generates a vivid scene with key vocabulary and suggested details
- `POST /scene-description/evaluate` ‚Äî Evaluates spoken description across 4 dimensions + WPM

Both use Pydantic models, `safe_llm_call`, `clamp_score`, rate limiting ‚Äî fully consistent with the ~30 existing Quick Practice endpoints.

**Frontend** (`QuickSceneDescriptionCard.tsx`): 241-line component with 4 phases (idle ‚Üí speaking ‚Üí evaluating ‚Üí done), 30s countdown timer, vocabulary hints, score display, model description reference. Uses `handleFinishRef` pattern to avoid stale closures ‚Äî correct approach.

**API client** (`api.ts`): Two typed interfaces + two fetch functions, matching existing patterns exactly.

**Hub integration** (`QuickPracticeHub.tsx`): One-line import + one-line render under Speaking tab (now 15 cards).

**Tests** (`test_scene_description_api.py`): 13 integration tests covering: default/custom/advanced difficulty, 422 validation (invalid difficulty, empty scene, empty transcript, zero duration), fallback values for missing LLM keys, vocabulary capping to 6, score clamping (out-of-range values), WPM calculation accuracy, non-numeric score fallbacks.

**No database changes** ‚Äî this is a stateless LLM feature, so no migration needed.

**E2E spec**: No new spec tests added for the frontend card.

