  "description": "Add a feature that lets users see real conversation excerpts where their vocabulary words appeared. This bridges isolated vocabulary study with authentic conversational usage, reinforcing word knowledge through context.\n\nBackend:\n1. In `app/dal/vocabulary.py`, add `get_word_conversation_contexts(db, word_text, limit=5)` that queries: SELECT m.content, m.role, m.created_at, c.topic, c.id as conversation_id FROM messages m JOIN conversations c ON m.conversation_id = c.id WHERE c.status = 'ended' AND LOWER(m.content) LIKE '%' || LOWER(?) || '%' ORDER BY m.created_at DESC LIMIT ?. This finds messages containing the vocabulary word.\n2. In `app/routers/vocabulary.py`, add `GET /api/vocabulary/{word_id}/contexts` endpoint that fetches the word text via `get_word()`, then calls the new DAL function, and returns `{ word_id, word, contexts: [{ conversation_id, topic, role, snippet, created_at }] }`. The snippet should be the full message content (truncated to 200 chars if needed) with the word highlighted by returning its character position.\n\nFrontend:\n3. In `frontend/src/api.ts`, add `getWordConversationContexts(wordId)` API call and `VocabConversationContext` interface.\n4. In `frontend/src/pages/Vocabulary.tsx`, in the quiz result phase where words and scores are displayed, add an expandable 'üí¨ Used in Conversations' button next to each word. When tapped, it fetches contexts and shows 1-3 real conversation excerpts with the word bolded, the topic label, and a speaker icon for TTS playback. Shows 'Not found in conversations yet ‚Äî try using it next time!' when empty, which motivates active vocabulary use.",
